Reasoning: The paper deals with compressed sensing and the properties of sensing matrices, which are topics covered in several arXiv CS sub-categories. The focus on the spark, NSP order, and RIP order suggests that the paper may belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of matrix operations and the study of matrix products may also suggest cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the exploration of the properties of deterministic and random constructions of sensing matrices may suggest cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
